ciscoSmeMIB.name: ciscoSmeMIB
ciscoSmeMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553 -NETS E-mail: cs-san@cisco.com
ciscoSmeMIB.description: MIB module to manage Storage Media Encryption (SME) service. SME is an encryption service provided by an encryption node residing on a linecard in a storage device. It receives clear-text data from host, encrypts it, then sends it to be written to tape or disk. It does the reverse in the opposite direction so the service is completely transparent to the host. The purpose of this service is to enhance data security in case the tape or disk is lost or stolen. As with any important service, user requires that it provides some level of fault tolerant in a graceful manner. SME provides this by allowing encryption nodes to be grouped into cluster. Nodes in the same cluster immediately pick up the work of a failed node so user does not see service disruption.

CiscoSmeInterfaceStatus.name: CiscoSmeInterfaceStatus
CiscoSmeInterfaceStatus.description: Operational state of the SME interface. 'unknown(1)' -- interface is in an unknown state 'initializing(2)' -- interface is being initialized 'offline(3)' -- interface is not active 'online(4)' -- interface is online and can be used

CiscoSmeClusterStatus.name: CiscoSmeClusterStatus
CiscoSmeClusterStatus.description: Operational state of the SME cluster 'unknown(1)' -- cluster is in an unknown state 'inactive(2)' -- cluster is not active 'degraded(3)' -- cluster has lost some of its members 'recovery(4)' -- cluster is recovering from membership lost 'active(5)' -- cluster is active

CiscoSmeClusterIndex.name: CiscoSmeClusterIndex
CiscoSmeClusterIndex.description: This denotes the globally unique index for a SME cluster. The value of the CiscoSmeClusterIndex is a thirty-two-octet unsigned integer value encoded in a network-byte order.

cSmeClusterTable.name: cSmeClusterTable
cSmeClusterTable.description: This table lists all the SME clusters that are configured on this device. As with any important service, user requires that it provides some level of fault tolerant in a graceful manner. SME provides this by allowing encryption nodes to be grouped into cluster. Nodes in the same cluster immediately pick up the work of a failed node so user does not see service disruption.

cSmeClusterEntry.name: cSmeClusterEntry
cSmeClusterEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cSmeClusterTable. Each row represents a SME cluster in the system and provides the runtime and configuration information of a cluster.

cSmeClusterId.name: cSmeClusterId
cSmeClusterId.description: Globally unique index that identifies a SME cluster. This index must be generated in such a way that the same value is never reused even after cluster has been deleted.

cSmeClusterName.name: cSmeClusterName
cSmeClusterName.description: The name of the SME cluster.

cSmeClusterState.name: cSmeClusterState
cSmeClusterState.description: The operational state of the SME cluster.

cSmeClusterMasterInetAddrType.name: cSmeClusterMasterInetAddrType
cSmeClusterMasterInetAddrType.description: The type of Internet address of the SME cluster master. The Internet address of SME cluster master is specified by the value of the corresponding instance of cSmeClusterMasterInetAddr.

cSmeClusterMasterInetAddr.name: cSmeClusterMasterInetAddr
cSmeClusterMasterInetAddr.description: The Internet address of the SME cluster master device. The type of this Internet address is determined by the value of the corresponding instance of cSmeClusterMasterInetAddrType.

cSmeClusterStorageType.name: cSmeClusterStorageType
cSmeClusterStorageType.description: This object specifies the storage type for this conceptual row.

cSmeClusterRowStatus.name: cSmeClusterRowStatus
cSmeClusterRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. There is no restriction on the value of other columns before a newly created row can be made active.

cSmeClusterMembersTable.name: cSmeClusterMembersTable
cSmeClusterMembersTable.description: This table lists the information of devices, local or remote, which are members of SME clusters configured on a device.

cSmeClusterMembersEntry.name: cSmeClusterMembersEntry
cSmeClusterMembersEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cSmeClusterMembersTable. Each row represents a member device within a specified SME Cluster.

cSmeMemberInetAddrType.name: cSmeMemberInetAddrType
cSmeMemberInetAddrType.description: The type of Internet address of a cluster member within a specified SME cluster. The Internet address of this device is specified by the value of the corresponding instance of cSmeMemberInetAddr.

cSmeMemberInetAddr.name: cSmeMemberInetAddr
cSmeMemberInetAddr.description: The Internet address of the cluster member device within a specified SME cluster. The type of this Internet address is determined by the value of the corresponding instance of cSmeMemberInetAddrType.

cSmeFabric.name: cSmeFabric
cSmeFabric.description: Refers to the name of physical fibre channel fabric in the SAN. A typical SAN deployment consists of a dual fabric topology which corresponds to two physical fabrics. In such a deployment, a VSAN and a cluster is configured in both fabrics to allow multi-pathing and redundancy. The user specifies the physical fabric to which a device belongs to when the cluster is configured.

cSmeIsMemberLocal.name: cSmeIsMemberLocal
cSmeIsMemberLocal.description: Identifies if the device is a local or remote member of this cluster. 'true' means this device is a local device. 'false' means this device is a remote device.

cSmeMemberIsMaster.name: cSmeMemberIsMaster
cSmeMemberIsMaster.description: Indicates if this device is currently the master of the SME cluster. The value 'true' means this device is the master. The value 'false' means this device is not the master. Devices in a cluster select one of the cluster member to be a master. The master is responsible for handling cluster membership.

cSmeClusterMemberStorageType.name: cSmeClusterMemberStorageType
cSmeClusterMemberStorageType.description: This object specifies the storage type for this conceptual row.

cSmeClusterMemberRowStatus.name: cSmeClusterMemberRowStatus
cSmeClusterMemberRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. There is no restriction on the value of other columns before a newly created row can be made active. When a cluster is deleted, all entries in this table should be purged automatically.

cSmeClusterMemberIfTable.name: cSmeClusterMemberIfTable
cSmeClusterMemberIfTable.description: This table lists the information of SME interfaces on all devices, local or remote, which are members of SME clusters configured on a device.

cSmeClusterMemberIfEntry.name: cSmeClusterMemberIfEntry
cSmeClusterMemberIfEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cSmeClusterMemberIfTable. Each row represents a participating interface on local/remote device member within the specified SME cluster.

cSmeClusterInterfaceIndex.name: cSmeClusterInterfaceIndex
cSmeClusterInterfaceIndex.description: A unique Interface index for a SME interface on a device in this cluster. This is the same as ifIndex of the ifTable of RFC1213.

cSmeClusterInterfaceState.name: cSmeClusterInterfaceState
cSmeClusterInterfaceState.description: The operational state of this SME interface.

cSmeInterfaceTable.name: cSmeInterfaceTable
cSmeInterfaceTable.description: This table lists all SME interfaces on the local device and its corresponding information.

cSmeInterfaceEntry.name: cSmeInterfaceEntry
cSmeInterfaceEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cSmeInterfaceTable. Each row represents a particular SME interface on a local device.

cSmeInterfaceIndex.name: cSmeInterfaceIndex
cSmeInterfaceIndex.description: A unique Interface index for a SME interface on this device. This is the same as ifIndex of the ifTable of RFC1213.

cSmeInterfaceState.name: cSmeInterfaceState
cSmeInterfaceState.description: Operational state of this SME interface.

cSmeInterfaceClusterId.name: cSmeInterfaceClusterId
cSmeInterfaceClusterId.description: Identifies the cluster to which this SME interface belongs.

cSmeInterfaceStorageType.name: cSmeInterfaceStorageType
cSmeInterfaceStorageType.description: This object specifies the storage type for this conceptual row.

cSmeInterfaceRowStatus.name: cSmeInterfaceRowStatus
cSmeInterfaceRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. There is no restriction on the value of other columns before a newly created row can be made active. For example, cSmeInterfaceClusterId column can be set independently later.

cSmeHostPortTable.name: cSmeHostPortTable
cSmeHostPortTable.description: This table lists the hosts that are configured for SME. In the case of application servers, the disks that are accessed by the hosts may be encrypted. In the case of backup/restore master/media servers, the tapes accessed by the hosts may be encrypted.

cSmeHostPortEntry.name: cSmeHostPortEntry
cSmeHostPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cSmeHostPortTable. Each row represents a particular host configured for SME service in a particular cluster.

cSmeHostPortName.name: cSmeHostPortName
cSmeHostPortName.description: Fibre-channel Port name (P_WWN) of the Host Nx_Port.

cSmeHostPortClusterId.name: cSmeHostPortClusterId
cSmeHostPortClusterId.description: Identifies the cluster to which this host port belongs.

cSmeHostPortStorageType.name: cSmeHostPortStorageType
cSmeHostPortStorageType.description: This object specifies the storage type for this conceptual row.

cSmeHostPortRowStatus.name: cSmeHostPortRowStatus
cSmeHostPortRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. There is no restriction on the value of other columns before a newly created row can be made active.

cSmeConfigTableLastChanged.name: cSmeConfigTableLastChanged
cSmeConfigTableLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when a change to any SME MIB table other than the cSmeHostPortTable last occurred.

cSmeHostPortTableLastChanged.name: cSmeHostPortTableLastChanged
cSmeHostPortTableLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when a change to cSmeHostPortTable last occurred.

cSmeNotifyEnable.name: cSmeNotifyEnable
cSmeNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies if the SME notifications should be generated or not. If the value of this object is 'true', then the notifications are generated. If the value of this object is 'false, then the notifications are not generated.

ciscoSmeInterfaceCreate.name: ciscoSmeInterfaceCreate
ciscoSmeInterfaceCreate.description: This notification is generated when a SME interface associated with a local device is created.

ciscoSmeInterfaceDelete.name: ciscoSmeInterfaceDelete
ciscoSmeInterfaceDelete.description: This notification is generated when a SME interface associated with a local device is deleted.

ciscoSmeClusterNewMaster.name: ciscoSmeClusterNewMaster
ciscoSmeClusterNewMaster.description: This notification is generated when the sending device who is participating in a SME cluster has transitioned to be the master of the cluster.

ciscoSmeMIBCompliance.name: ciscoSmeMIBCompliance
ciscoSmeMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement SME.

ciscoSmeConfigGroup.name: ciscoSmeConfigGroup
ciscoSmeConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects for SME configuration.

ciscoSmeNotifControlGroup.name: ciscoSmeNotifControlGroup
ciscoSmeNotifControlGroup.description: A collection of objects for controlling SME notification.

ciscoSmeNotifsGroup.name: ciscoSmeNotifsGroup
ciscoSmeNotifsGroup.description: A collection of objects for notification of SME events.
